The paper discusses a framework for high-definition mapping using sensors such as GNSS and visual cameras, which is relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of visual observations and map-based geo-localization also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The collaborative aspect of the framework, with multiple vehicles contributing to the map updates, could be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG) or a control systems problem (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of cloud servers for processing, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
